    <div class=\"letter-container\">\n  <div class=\"letter-paper\">\n    <article class=\"post h-entry\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\">\n\n      <header class=\"post-header\">\n        <h1 class=\"post-title p-name\" itemprop=\"name headline\">Why do you want to be productive?</h1>\n        <p class=\"post-meta\">\n          <time class=\"dt-published\" datetime=\"2021-12-01T00:00:00+00:00\" itemprop=\"datePublished\">Dec 1, 2021\n          </time></p>\n      </header>\n\n      <div class=\"post-content e-content\" itemprop=\"articleBody\">\n        <p>The most important question to ask when you are working on improving your productivity is why do you want to be productive in the first place?</p>\n\n<p>Productivity is about effeciency; getting more done with your time. If you are being more productive at work and have a few extra hours at the end of the day, how will you spend those hours?</p>\n\n<p>I like being productive with my time so that I don‚Äôt have to spent all my time at work and can utilise my hours post 7PM on spending time with my wife/ reading books/ advising other startups/ / shitposting on Twitter.</p>\n\n<p>I care about <a href=\"https://manassaloi.com/2020/03/31/80-20.html\">Pareto‚Äôing my life</a> because I want to do more things in a day. We all have the same number of hours. So unless you know why you want to squeese out a few free ones at the end of the day, you won‚Äôt focus on building systems that will get you more output from the time spent at work.</p>\n\n      </div><a class=\"u-url\" href=\"/2021/12/01/productivity-hours.html\" hidden></a>\n    </article>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n      </div>\n    </main><footer class=\"site-footer h-card\">\n  <data class=\"u-url\" href=\"/\"></data>\n\n  <div class=\"wrapper\">\n\n    <div class=\"footer-col-wrapper\">\n      <div class=\"footer-col one-half\">\n      <p class=\"footer-heading\"> Powered by <a href=\"https://jekyllrb.com\">Jekyll</a> and <a href=\"https://github.c